The Lokum – Anatolia & Beyond
The Lokum is a high-end, premium restaurant website designed to showcase the "Fire & Tradition" of Anatolian and Turkish cuisine. Located in Bengaluru, India, the digital experience mirrors the restaurant's focus on heritage, inherited techniques, and authentic Turkish hospitality.

🍽️ Project Overview
The website serves as a luxury digital storefront featuring:

Immersive Visuals: High-quality video backgrounds and cinematic zoom effects in the hero section.

Brand Philosophy: A dedicated "Our Story" section detailing the restaurant's origins and culinary intention.

Seasonal Features: Integrated Ramzan Special sections highlighting curated platters and traditional dishes.

Digital Menu: A standalone, interactive menu page designed for high visual impact.

Premium Interactions: Sophisticated animations and smooth scrolling powered by GSAP.

 Key Features
1. Advanced Animation System
The site utilizes the GreenSock Animation Platform (GSAP) and ScrollTrigger for high-performance, scroll-based animations.

Smooth Scrolling: Implementation of ScrollSmoother for a luxurious browsing feel.

Dynamic Gallery: An "Ultra Smooth Gallery" with 3D perspective shifts and active item scaling.

Interactive Navigation: A responsive navbar that adapts on scroll and includes an asymmetric hamburger menu with unique "X" transitions.

2. Specialized Components
Ramzan Offer Popup: A timed, auto-opening popup for seasonal promotions with built-in auto-close functionality.

Iftar Timer: Real-time logic for countdowns during the Ramzan season.

Image Modal Viewer: A custom modal system for high-resolution menu viewing.

Lazy Loading: Native intersection observers to optimize image loading performance.

3. Luxury Design Aesthetic
Color Palette: Deep blacks (#0a0908), soft creams (#efe4d8), and bronze/gold accents (#c08a50).

Typography: An elegant pairing of Playfair Display (Serif) for headings and Inter (Sans-serif) for body text.

Technical Stack
HTML5: Semantic structure for SEO and accessibility.

CSS3 (Post-modern): Utilizes CSS variables, complex gradients, 3D transforms, and advanced backdrop filters.

JavaScript (ES6+): Custom modular architecture with an Immediately Invoked Function Expression (IIFE) for scope protection.

Libraries:

GSAP (Core): Animation engine.

ScrollTrigger: Scroll-based interaction.

ScrollSmoother: Premium scrolling physics.

📁 File Structure
index.html: The primary landing page containing the story, gallery, and seasonal sections.

menu.html: The visual menu experience with floating background textures.

style.css: The central design system containing luxury variables and responsive layout logic.

script.js: The engine managing animations, popups, and interactive navigation.

 Setup Instructions
Clone the repository to your local environment.

Asset Hosting: Ensure the images/ and videos/ folders contain the high-quality media referenced in the HTML (e.g., logo-web.png, fallback-bg.jpg, and the hero MP4).

Local Server: Due to GSAP's ScrollTrigger and external script loading, it is recommended to run the project via a local server (like Live Server in VS Code) for the best performance.

